National Training Specialist (code: NTS)
Responsibilities
The purpose of the National Training Officer role is to provide oversight, technical guidance and implementation support for training content development and delivery via Technical Assistance Training Teams (TATTs) within an anticipated USAID-funded project:  “Improving Disaster Preparedness and Disaster Management Capacity in Indonesia” (the Project) Requirements: Management, or a Bachelor’s degree with commensurate experience (5+ years)5 years experience in project management, supervision, administration, and implementationExperience in implementation of training projects funded by institutional grant donorsDeep knowledge in TOT, training design, adult learning and training evaluationGood leadership and communication skillsExperience in managing inter-agency consortia and/or partnersFluent in English and Bahasa Indonesia, both verbal and written
Requirements
